<table cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" width="100%" bgcolor="#9B7F11">
<tr bgcolor="#323741"><td>
<table width="100%">
<tr><td class="header">World of Warcraft looking to be the next big thing!</td>
<td class="headerblue" align="right">30-05-2003 22:14</td></tr>
</table>
</td></tr>
<tr><td bgcolor="#424954">
While Shadowbane, EQ and surely Planetside take much of our gaming time, we always look to the future.  Will it be EQ2 for us?   I am not so sure.  Skuttlebutt sayeth that EQ2 will again not be oriented around PvP whilst World of Warcraft has some other ideas.  <br />
<br />
After looking over at WoW (World of Warcraft) for sometime, we came to the conclusion that this game may very well be the next big thing to unite all of Darkenbane under one game!   With this in mind, I have taken the liberty of putting up a new message board for WoW discussion and Meter has already posted a nice quote from a WoW developer as follows:<br />
<br />
'That doesn't mean you can't share some encounters with your opponents. Blizzard hopes you will, specifically in the player-versus-player areas. 90 per cent of the world will remain non-PvP, but the rest will encourage you to clash with your opponents for the game's best cosmetic items, as well as experience points. "There will be only rewards, no disincentive to PvP," explained Adham. He continued with a joking illustration: "For example, in a non-PvP zone, you might be able to get an AC20 shield, but it has a care bear on the front. In a PvP zone, you can get an AC20 shield, but it's black." The PvP rules will follow the Horde vs. Alliance rules, with the good races facing those of a darker ilk. Adham took pains to point out that PvP would be consensual only, making up a small but interesting part of the world, although there would be full-PvP servers.' <br />
<br />
Per Meter's post the entire article where this quote was found is <a href="http://www.gamesdomain.com/gdreview...ay03/WoW_1.html"><i>here.</i></a><br />
<br />
-Grayrage D'Bane</td></tr>
